# **OASIS ROFL – Full Deployment Tutorial (Improved)**

## **1. Import your wallet**

```
oasis wallet import "YOUR_PUBLIC_KEY"
```

---

## **2. Initialize the ROFL project**

```
oasis rofl init
```

---

## **3. Create the app on the Sapphire testnet (only once)**

```
oasis rofl create --network testnet
```

---

## **4. Prepare your application for deployment**

### **4.1 Your application must be fully working locally**

* Complete code
* All environment variables ready
* All backend routes tested

### **4.2 Prepare a proper Dockerfile**

Your Dockerfile must include **everything required** to run your app inside Docker.

---

## **5. Build your Docker image !!!(required: linux/amd64)!!!**

```
docker build --platform linux/amd64 -t juanlarraya/linda-rofl-backend:latest .
```

---

## **6. Push your image to Docker Hub you will need a (Fully Qualified Domain Name (FQDN))**

```
docker push juanlarraya/linda-rofl-backend:latest
```

This is required because ROFL deploys using a **Fully Qualified Domain Name (FQDN)** of the image.

---

## **7. Update your docker-compose.yaml**

Modify the service image field:

```
image: "docker.io/juanlarraya/linda-rofl-backend:latest"
```

**Important:**
✔ Open the ports your app needs
✔ Expose them with `ports:`

Example:

```yaml
ports:
  - "3000:3000"
```

---

## **8. Follow the Oasis ROFL Quickstart**

Reference:
[https://docs.oasis.io/build/rofl/quickstart](https://docs.oasis.io/build/rofl/quickstart)

---

## **9. Build the ROFL bundle**

### **On Linux**

```
oasis rofl build
```

### **On macOS / Windows (using container)**

```
docker run --platform linux/amd64 --volume .:/src -it ghcr.io/oasisprotocol/rofl-dev:main oasis rofl build
```

This command generates the **bundle** used to deploy to Sapphire.

---

## **10. Update the deployed app**

```
oasis rofl update
```

---

## **11. Deploy the updated version**

```
oasis rofl deploy
```

---

## **12. If your app does NOT start**

Use machine logs:

```
oasis rofl machine logs
```

Look for:

* Container startup errors
* Port binding issues
* Invalid configuration
* Error codes from ROFL


  
